WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.816
Your music app just played you a song you love, by a band you have never heard of.

2
00:00:05.816 --> 00:00:10.214
Somewhere in a data center, two lists of numbers got compared,

3
00:00:10.214 --> 00:00:12.767
and the comparison said: same taste.

4
00:00:12.767 --> 00:00:15.392
So here is the question of the night.

5
00:00:15.392 --> 00:00:19.222
How do you score a match between two lists of numbers?

6
00:00:19.222 --> 00:00:20.570
Hold that question.

7
00:00:20.570 --> 00:00:24.400
One answer to it runs half of modern machine learning.

8
00:00:24.400 --> 00:00:25.618
Strip it down.

9
00:00:25.618 --> 00:00:29.882
A taste is an arrow: each direction is a quality,

10
00:00:29.882 --> 00:00:34.320
and the length is how hard the song leans that way.

11
00:00:34.320 --> 00:00:38.410
Take one probe arrow and four candidate arrows.

12
00:00:38.410 --> 00:00:41.630
Multiply them entry by entry and add.

13
00:00:41.630 --> 00:00:44.154
That single sum is the score.

14
00:00:44.154 --> 00:00:49.897
Before you drag anything, call it: which candidate ends up on top,

15
00:00:49.897 --> 00:00:52.594
and does any score go negative?

16
00:00:52.594 --> 00:00:56.510
Now turn the probe and watch the bars answer.

17
00:00:56.510 --> 00:01:00.165
Point at a candidate and its score climbs.

18
00:01:00.165 --> 00:01:02.080
Turn away and it dies.

19
00:01:02.080 --> 00:01:06.518
So a big score means two songs are the same, right?

20
00:01:06.518 --> 00:01:07.562
Watch again.

21
00:01:07.562 --> 00:01:12.348
The bars moved while the candidates never moved at all.

22
00:01:12.348 --> 00:01:16.960
The score reads agreement of direction, not sameness.

23
00:01:17.065 --> 00:01:20.094
Look at what your hands just learned.

24
00:01:20.094 --> 00:01:24.432
Point the probe along a candidate and the sum climbs.

25
00:01:24.432 --> 00:01:27.788
Point it across and the sum dies to zero.

26
00:01:27.788 --> 00:01:31.308
Point it against and the sum goes negative.

27
00:01:31.308 --> 00:01:36.301
One multiply and add, and it behaves like a meter with agree,

28
00:01:36.301 --> 00:01:38.839
ignore, and oppose on the dial.

29
00:01:38.839 --> 00:01:43.505
So say it plainly: the dot product is a similarity meter.

30
00:01:43.505 --> 00:01:45.715
Two lists of numbers go in.

31
00:01:45.715 --> 00:01:49.153
One honest reading of alignment comes out.

32
00:01:49.153 --> 00:01:55.865
And the reading tracks direction, because direction is all the sweep ever changed.

33
00:01:55.865 --> 00:01:57.673
Time to close the loop.

34
00:01:57.673 --> 00:02:01.447
Rebuild the meter from memory: two arrows go in,

35
00:02:01.447 --> 00:02:05.220
so what two operations turn them into the score?

36
00:02:05.220 --> 00:02:10.488
While you think, keep the meter running and walk it one aisle over.

37
00:02:10.488 --> 00:02:16.620
Same needle, same recipe, we just point it at a job posting instead of a song.

38
00:02:16.620 --> 00:02:22.359
Score yourself against what the role wants: multiply the matched entries,

39
00:02:22.359 --> 00:02:25.189
add them up, one number for the fit.

40
00:02:25.189 --> 00:02:30.063
Nothing about the meter changed, only the shelf it is reading.

41
00:02:30.063 --> 00:02:34.466
The multiply-and-add never asked what the numbers meant,

42
00:02:34.466 --> 00:02:37.218
and that is exactly why it travels.

43
00:02:37.218 --> 00:02:40.991
Now the honest look, and guess before you watch.

44
00:02:40.991 --> 00:02:44.214
If a candidate's numbers just get bigger,

45
00:02:44.214 --> 00:02:48.302
same direction, longer arrow, does its score change?

46
00:02:48.302 --> 00:02:49.089
It climbs.

47
00:02:49.089 --> 00:02:53.491
The direction never moved, and the score climbed anyway.

48
00:02:53.491 --> 00:03:00.174
Long songs would win on sheer loudness, and padded resumes would win on sheer length.

49
00:03:00.174 --> 00:03:06.306
So the meter has a gap with a shape: it cannot tell direction apart from size.

50
00:03:06.306 --> 00:03:09.844
That is the thread to pull for the walk home.

51
00:03:09.844 --> 00:03:12.517
If the score keeps rewarding size,

52
00:03:12.517 --> 00:03:18.098
what is the cheapest fix that keeps the direction and forgets the size?

53
00:03:18.098 --> 00:03:18.806
Still up?

54
00:03:18.806 --> 00:03:22.265
The menu below has three ways to keep going.
